<setup>
  <function name="Ax">$AxExp</function>
</setup>
<p>
    Consider the function <m>A</m> defined by the rule
    <me>
      A(x) = \int_1^x f(t) \, dt
    </me>
    where <m>f(t) = 4-2t</m>.
<!--    is illustrated below. -->

<!--    <graph>
     <line draggable="false" slope="-2" through="(0,4)"/>
   </graph> -->

    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Compute <m>A(1)</m> and <m>A(2)</m> exactly.
        </p>
        <p><m>A(1)=</m><answer>0</answer></p>
        <p><m>A(2)=</m><answer>1</answer></p>
<!--         <p><m>A(3)=</m><answer>0</answer></p> -->
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Use the First Fundamental Theorem of Calculus to find a formula for
          <m>A(x)</m> that does not involve integrals;
          that is, use the first FTC to evaluate <m>\int_1^x (4-2t) \, dt</m>.
          Once your formula is correct, the new formula will be used to check the values of <m>A(1)</m> and <m>A(2)</m> found in (a).
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>A(x)=</m><answer name="AxExp">4x-x^2-3</answer>
        
        </p>
        <p>
          <conditionalContent condition="$AxExp.creditAchieved=1">
            <p><m>A(1)=$$Ax(1)</m></p>
            <p><m>A(2)=$$Ax(2)</m></p>
          </conditionalContent>
        </p>  
      
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Observe that <m>f</m> is a linear function;
          what kind of function is <m>A</m>?
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>A</m> is <answer><choiceInput inline>
            <choice>?</choice>
            <choice>linear</choice>
            <choice credit="1">quadratic</choice>
            <choice>cubic</choice>
            <choice>exponential</choice>
          </choiceInput></answer>.  
        </p>  
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Using the formula <m>A(x)=</m><mathInput disabled><conditionalContent condition="$AxExp.creditAchieved=1">$AxExp</conditionalContent></mathInput>
          you found in (b), determine <m>A'(x)</m>.
        </p>
        <p><m>A'(x)=</m><answer name="ApxExp">4-2x</answer></p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Recall from the original formula for <m>A</m> that <m>f(t)=4-2t</m>.  State eh corresponding expression for <m>f(x)</m>.
        </p>
        <p><m>f(x)=</m><answer name="fxExp">4-2x</answer></p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Given your conclusions that
          <m>A'(x)=</m><mathInput disabled><conditionalContent condition="$ApxExp.creditAchieved=1">$ApxExp</conditionalContent></mathInput> and
          <m>f(x)=</m><mathInput disabled><conditionalContent condition="$fxExp.creditAchieved=1">$fxExp</conditionalContent></mathInput>, complete the following sentence to state what appears to be the relationship between <m>A(x)=\int_1^x f(t)\,dt</m> and <m>f(x)</m> in general.
        </p>
        <p>  
          From our work in this specific example, we conjecture that if <m>A(x)=\int_1^x f(t)\,dt</m>, then <answer><choiceInput inline>
            <choice>?</choice>
            <choice>A'(x) = f(t)</choice>
            <choice>A'(x) = f'(x)</choice>
            <choice credit="1">A'(x) = f(x)</choice>
            <choice>A'(x) = f'(t)</choice>
          </choiceInput></answer>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>